name: Gyan Yankovich
bio: Lifestyle Editor @sydneymorningherald @theageaustralia ✍🏼 Author of Just Friends @ultimopress 📖

social_posts.post_text: It was such a joy to talk to @stephclairesmith and @laura.henshaw about their friendship for the first @sundaylifeau of 2023.
One of my all-time favourite (and funniest) interviews: @chloe.fisher and @followthefishtv for the cover of today’s @sundaylifeau 🤍

I'm incredibly excited to share that... I'm writing a book! Just Friends is a non-fiction book about what it means to be, to make, to have, and to lose a friend. It's about the way our friends shape our lives and asks why our friendships are constantly being devalued by society, always coming second to the relationships we have with our family and romantic partners. In many ways, it feels like I've been working on this book for years, as I've found myself constantly circling the topic of friendship in my work and in my personal life. Friendship is my favourite thing to talk and write about, so I feel extremely lucky to be able to spend the next year doing just that. Just Friends will be published by @ultimopress in February 2024 and, I'm sorry, but I will be talking about it a lot between now and then.
Nine years of celebrating birthdays together, and they just get better and better 🪩
I started my new job as Lifestyle Editor at the @sydneymorningherald and @theageaustralia today and I couldn’t be happier!!!

I've officially submitted the first draft of my first book! I can't describe what a privilege it's been to spend the last year reading, talking, and writing about my favourite subject. I feel so ridiculously lucky, it's hard to put it all into words.

Just Friends is dedicated to my friends. The ones who have listened, checked-in, and celebrated every tiny milestone. I owe you all the world. 

And a final thank you to @_michaelconroy_, the most patient person to ever share a home with someone trying to figure out how to write a book 🤍

I can't quite believe the time has come to reveal the cover of Just Friends!

This cover, designed by the talented @_georgesaad, reflects what I hope this book will remind us all: that it's bold to care deeply about friendship; that these relationships are worthy of our attention; and that, when invited, our friends can weave themselves into every part of our lives. 

Just Friends is available to pre-order now! Ask your favourite bookshop or head to the link in my bio.

And, most importantly, tell your friends! 😌

I got to spend a perfect afternoon talking to @zamcdonald and @michelleandrews1 about good advice, our lost pandemic years, the attention economy, and, of course, @shamelessmedia for the cover story of today’s @sundaylifeau. There’s much more I wish I could have fit in, but thankfully there is so much wisdom squeezed into their new book, 4am, which is out so soon!

The final version of my little book goes off to print this week, but these pretty advanced copies have already started landing in people’s homes, offices, and weekend-away bags. I’m sure this won’t be the last time I mention it, but Just Friends is now available to pre-order at the link in my bio 🥹

Last night I met the most wonderful group of book lovers, who all share their favourite reads here on Instagram, at a perfect event thrown by my incredible publisher @ultimopress. I will eventually stop spamming you all, but I will never get over these bespoke friendship candy hearts everyone got in their goodie bags 🥹
It’s a real book! And I feel very overwhelmed, to say the least! Just Friends is out on January 31 (and available to pre-order right this second) 💜💚

My book is coming to the US with a new title, Friendship First, and another amazing publisher.

So many of the conversations and situations that inspired this book happened while I was living in New York. The friends and editors I met and worked with (especially the editors who became friends) shaped both the way I write and how I think about friendship today. I feel so lucky this little part of me is finding its way back there.

Friendship First will be out in fall 2024. As always, I’m feeling very overwhelmed 🥹

A book! In a bar! What could be better? To celebrate the launch of Just Friends in Sydney we’re going to be in conversation at a Books in Bars @dymocksbooks event on Tuesday, February 6. Bring a friend, have a drink, we promise it will be fun! Tickets are available now at the link in our bios. 🍸
Lifestyle Editor @sydneymorningherald @theageaustralia ✍🏼 Author of Just Friends @ultimopress 📖
